00:14:28,890 --> 00:14:30,950
Okay,we keep the building sealed.

265
00:14:31,010 --> 00:14:32,960
I want all the guests moved into holding rooms.

266
00:14:33,030 --> 00:14:34,750
Tell D.C. police we're keeping jurisdiction.

267
00:14:34,830 --> 00:14:35,410
We need to talk.

268
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:36,480
YES,SIR. LET'S GO.

269
00:14:37,950 --> 00:14:39,120
The shooter is in the building.

270
00:14:39,590 --> 00:14:40,930
Now,we don't know whether he's armed or not,

271
00:14:40,990 --> 00:14:43,120
but I've got 250 wedding guests as suspects.

272
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:44,530
Actually,that's not true.

273
00:14:44,580 --> 00:14:46,370
Men commit 90% of gun homicides.

274
00:14:46,810 --> 00:14:48,430
Most of them are between 17 and 49.

275
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:50,600
Odds are you got a male under 50.

276
00:14:50,670 --> 00:14:52,970
Narrows it down to, what,150 people?

277
00:14:53,050 --> 00:14:54,870
All right,whatever it is, I need your help.

278
00:14:54,950 --> 00:14:56,130
Now,I've got 12 agents.

279
00:14:56,180 --> 00:14:57,380
With all the VIPs here,

280
00:14:57,460 --> 00:15:00,600
it's gonna be hard to keep this building shut down for more than an hour or two.

281
00:15:00,660 --> 00:15:02,660
Do you still think that somebody was trying to kill the ambassador?

282
00:15:02,740 --> 00:15:03,660
Well,if this is somebody

283
00:15:03,700 --> 00:15:06,450
slick enough to smuggle a gun in here, assume he hit his target.

284
00:15:06,530 --> 00:15:08,290
Now,this is somebody who wanted to kill the groom.

285
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,670
Getting in here took planning.

286
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:11,860
If the motive is personal,

287
00:15:11,910 --> 00:15:13,450
it's probably a long-standing grievance.

288
00:15:13,510 --> 00:15:14,830
Lots of suppressed anger.

289
00:15:16,260 --> 00:15:17,370
The person you're looking for,

290
00:15:17,430 --> 00:15:19,510
had to hide his feelings until the groom arrived.

291
00:15:19,580 --> 00:15:21,390
Some of that emotion must've leaked out.

292
00:15:21,470 --> 00:15:23,700
Get the tape from the videographers and,uh,

293
00:15:23,730 --> 00:15:27,340
isolate any,uh,suppressed anger,fear,contempt.

294
00:15:27,780 --> 00:15:29,640
Did the family mention a threat to the groom?

295
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,490
Not a word. Uh,somebody's lying.

296
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:33,550
Talk to people who knew the groom.

297
00:15:33,630 --> 00:15:35,180
Look for signs of concealment.

298
00:15:35,620 --> 00:15:37,080
Somebody who seems to be holding something back.

299
00:15:37,130 --> 00:15:38,370
You going to talk to the parents?

300
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:40,150
If you're looking for lies, you start at the top.

301
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,090
Hey.

302
00:15:42,110 --> 00:15:43,690
Aronson told me to give you any help that you need.

303
00:15:44,550 --> 00:15:45,210
I'm Karl.

304
00:15:45,970 --> 00:15:46,650
Karl Dupree.

305
00:15:48,420 --> 00:15:49,200
Aronson sent you?

306
00:15:49,660 --> 00:15:50,340
That's right.

307
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:51,950
No,it isn't.

308
00:15:52,760 --> 00:15:54,420
You asked him if you could work with me,right?

309
00:15:55,910 --> 00:15:57,220
Not much gets past you,does it?

310
00:15:58,160 --> 00:15:59,370
You have no idea.

311
00:16:01,510 --> 00:16:02,160
Let's go.

312
00:16:10,090 --> 00:16:10,860
Mrs. Park?

313
00:16:12,380 --> 00:16:14,000
Hi,I'm Gillian Foster.

314
00:16:14,070 --> 00:16:15,120
This is Cal Lightman.

315
00:16:16,620 --> 00:16:17,150
How do you do?

316
00:16:18,290 --> 00:16:20,810
We're working with the Secret Service to try and figure out what happened.

317
00:16:21,930 --> 00:16:23,440
How's Won-Hee doing?

318
00:16:24,190 --> 00:16:25,090
Uh,we don't know.

319
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:26,970
He just got out of surgery.

320
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,460
They're moving him to the ICU.

321
00:16:28,870 --> 00:16:30,710
We thought someone was going to try to hurt the ambassador.

322
00:16:31,140 --> 00:16:34,470
But it looks like whoever shot your husband was trying to hurt him.

323
00:16:34,990 --> 00:16:36,600
Do you know why somebody would want to do that?

324
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:37,730
I don't understand.

325
00:16:37,760 --> 00:16:40,040
I thought this was a political issue about his father.

326
00:16:40,290 --> 00:16:41,730
It doesn't look like that anymore.

327
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:44,400
Did he ever mention anyone threatening him?

328
00:16:45,220 --> 00:16:46,280
Threatening him?

329
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:48,820
Uh,no.

330
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:51,380
No,are you sure about this?

331
00:16:52,210 --> 00:16:53,380
What were you just thinking?

332
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:55,670
Excuse me?

333
00:16:56,790 --> 00:16:58,510
Something just went through your mind,what was it?

334
00:16:59,860 --> 00:17:00,920
I-I don't know.

335
00:17:01,810 --> 00:17:02,950
Ma'am,I can take you

336
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:03,930
to your husband now.

337
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:05,560
I have to go.

338
00:17:05,560 --> 00:17:06,380
Dr. Seagal,

339
00:17:08,790 --> 00:17:11,470
Dr. David Seagal to O.R. Six,please.

340
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:13,120
Additional cognitive processing.

341
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:13,940
The eye flutter.

342
00:17:15,070 --> 00:17:16,630
There's something she's not telling us.

343
00:17:16,690 --> 00:17:19,100
Or she's freaked out because she just heard her husband was targeted

344
00:17:19,160 --> 00:17:20,850
for assassination on their wedding day.

345
00:17:21,960 --> 00:17:22,570
Could be.

346
00:17:23,070 --> 00:17:24,790
We're professional videographers.

347
00:17:25,810 --> 00:17:27,130
You're not part of the families,

348
00:17:27,190 --> 00:17:28,710
we,uh,we cannot give you the tapes.

349
00:17:28,780 --> 00:17:30,940
Uh,we're trying to figure out who shot the groom.

350
00:17:31,380 --> 00:17:33,530
Which I'm pretty sure the families support.

351
00:17:33,590 --> 00:17:34,890
Sorry,we have--

352
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:40,550
There's a contract that strictly forbids releasing the footage.

353
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:41,820
Nothing I can do.

354
00:17:42,340 --> 00:17:45,750
Yeah,see,those hesitations and repetitions,

355
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:47,650
you're having trouble processing what you're saying

356
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:49,360
which typically means you're lying.

357
00:17:49,830 --> 00:17:51,330
I'll bet your contract doesn't say anything.

358
00:17:52,180 --> 00:17:53,760
You want to take a look at the footage,

359
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:56,310
because you want to see if the shooting is on there.

360
00:17:56,390 --> 00:17:59,730
Because if it is,you're gonna sell it to the tabloid that writes the fattest check.

361
00:18:00,110 --> 00:18:00,620
Right?

362
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:02,670
You're trying to get the guy who did this?

363
00:18:03,310 --> 00:18:03,900
That's right.

364
00:18:05,030 --> 00:18:05,750
Don't be an idiot,man.

365
00:18:05,820 --> 00:18:06,660
Give him the tapes.

366
00:18:07,510 --> 00:18:08,110
Let's go.

367
00:18:11,760 --> 00:18:14,780
Any of this footage shows up on the net,

368
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:18,020
I'm gonna rip your head off and stuff it down your throat.

369
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:19,500
No hesitation.

370
00:18:19,580 --> 00:18:20,860
Now you're telling the truth.

371
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:27,120
Who would want to kill my son?

372
00:18:27,180 --> 00:18:28,440
We're trying to find that out.

373
00:18:28,870 --> 00:18:29,630
You're mistaken.

374
00:18:30,740 --> 00:18:32,580
If there was a second assassin in the room,

375
00:18:32,670 --> 00:18:34,260
well,then,two were sent after me.

376
00:18:34,320 --> 00:18:35,550
This had nothing to do with my family.

377
00:18:36,530 --> 00:18:37,540
You sure about that?

378
00:18:38,650 --> 00:18:40,380
Politics was behind this,

379
00:18:41,510 --> 00:18:42,740
People who want to silence me.

380
00:18:43,850 --> 00:18:45,420
That is who you should be looking for.

381
00:18:49,610 --> 00:18:51,580
A finger tells you so much,doesn't it?

382
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:54,140
Yeah,it pointed one way while his eyes were pointed another.

383
00:18:54,180 --> 00:18:55,400
That happens when you're lying.

384
00:18:55,470 --> 00:18:57,360
Your mind's working so hard to make stuff up,

385
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:59,040
that your body can't keep in sync.

386
00:19:00,370 --> 00:19:04,500
I did not have sexual relations with that woman.

387
00:19:05,860 --> 00:19:07,640
<i>These tapes are from the videographers at the wedding.</i>

388
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:10,080
Most of the footage is for the hour before the shooting,

389
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:12,600
so,you're not likely to see any overt anger or fear.

390
00:19:13,340 --> 00:19:15,220
We're looking for someone trying to hide those feelings.

391
00:19:15,270 --> 00:19:16,320
Since it's a wedding, and pretty much

392
00:19:16,340 --> 00:19:18,310
everyone is pretending they're having a good time,

393
00:19:18,690 --> 00:19:20,490
you're gonna see a lot of people hiding their feelings.

394
00:19:20,550 --> 00:19:22,520
And that means masking smiles.

395
00:19:24,530 --> 00:19:25,580
We're looking for these.

396
00:19:25,630 --> 00:19:26,720
The fear smile,

397
00:19:28,530 --> 00:19:29,140
Anger.

398
00:19:30,250 --> 00:19:31,190
And contempt.

399
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,030
Find anyone displaying one of these,

400
00:19:33,070 --> 00:19:34,340
flag it and bring it to me right away.

401
00:19:34,780 --> 00:19:36,240
We have exactly no time to do this.

402
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:46,230
Uh,we need to know if the groom mentioned anyone...

403
00:19:46,280 --> 00:19:47,960
...mentioned anyone threatening him.

404
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:49,250
Or speaking to a man...

405
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:51,290
The name of the bride and the groom,anybody threatening,

406
00:19:51,340 --> 00:19:53,400
anyone,anything causing him any trouble?

407
00:19:54,120 --> 00:19:55,010
Even something minor?

408
00:19:55,070 --> 00:19:56,260
I can't think of anything.

409
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:57,340
He was happy.

410
00:19:57,860 --> 00:19:59,300
Crazy in love with Phoebe.

411
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:00,890
That's all he talked about.

412
00:20:02,410 --> 00:20:03,500
He say anything different to you?

413
00:20:04,950 --> 00:20:05,400
No.

414
00:20:07,420 --> 00:20:08,290
Didn't mention anything.

415
00:20:10,430 --> 00:20:11,350
You're the best man,right?

416
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:12,680
What's your name?

417
00:20:13,460 --> 00:20:14,970
Garrett. Garrett Craywood.

418
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:18,780
Who are you calling?

419
00:20:19,530 --> 00:20:21,280
CIA,see what they got on the ambassador.

420
00:20:21,330 --> 00:20:22,350
Well,you know that's going to be classified.

421
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:23,790
Who's your contact? Laura.

422
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:24,450
Laura who?

423
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:25,720
Laura of the CIA.

424
00:20:26,390 --> 00:20:26,750
Hey.

425
00:20:27,690 --> 00:20:29,050
Hey,what are you doing here?

426
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:30,290
I thought you were leaving right after the ceremony.

427
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:31,380
I didn't get out in time.

428
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:32,650
Oh,I'm sorry, but I have to...

429
00:20:33,580 --> 00:20:34,710
I have to make this meeting at Reston.

430
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:35,780
I told Tolliver I'd cover.

431
00:20:35,810 --> 00:20:36,900
It's important I don't let him down.

432
00:20:36,940 --> 00:20:38,090
Just walk me out,okay?

433
00:20:38,490 --> 00:20:39,330
What... what do you mean?

434
00:20:40,330 --> 00:20:42,010
Tell the Secret Service guy I can go.

435
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:44,480
I can't do that.

436
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:45,180
Sure,you can.

437
00:20:45,230 --> 00:20:46,060
You're in charge,right?

438
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:48,170
Jill,it's important.

439
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:49,730
One person gets walked out,

440
00:20:49,770 --> 00:20:50,560
and everybody's going to try.

441
00:20:50,580 --> 00:20:52,250
We're not going to be able to keep the place sealed.

442
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:55,780
Never mind.

443
00:20:55,870 --> 00:20:56,650
I'll call the office.

444
00:20:58,460 --> 00:20:59,290
Come find me when you're done.

445
00:21:06,650 --> 00:21:08,520
What did Laura of the CIA have to say?

446
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:10,210
She'll get back to me.

447
00:21:10,430 --> 00:21:10,770
Hey.

448
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:12,310
You wanted somebody concealing something?

449
00:21:12,370 --> 00:21:14,290
The best man lied when I asked about the groom.

450
00:21:16,850 --> 00:21:20,640
Um,first,I wanted to say that Won-Hee and I

451
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:22,430
met our freshman year at Columbia.

452
00:21:22,510 --> 00:21:24,250
This is from the rehearsal dinner last night.

453
00:21:24,310 --> 00:21:27,070
Uh,he was into Mozart and poetry,

454
00:21:27,110 --> 00:21:29,670
and he liked to volunteer at the homeless shelter.

455
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:32,210
I,on the other hand, was into...

456
00:21:32,250 --> 00:21:33,550
You talked to Craywood earlier.

457
00:21:33,590 --> 00:21:35,380
Notice anything different from the way he sounded then?

458
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:40,250
I think his voice is higher pitched here.

459
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:42,290
He's definitely talking faster.

460
00:21:42,490 --> 00:21:44,130
That means his emotions are heightened.

461
00:21:44,910 --> 00:21:46,440
Maybe he's trying to control his anger.

462
00:21:47,610 --> 00:21:50,860
He's,uh... he's the most generous guy...

463
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:51,770
Oh,stop it there.

464
00:21:54,130 --> 00:21:55,470
Move in on his right hand.

465
00:22:00,220 --> 00:22:02,050
Here's a question you don't usually hear at a wedding.

466
00:22:03,910 --> 00:22:06,170
Why is the best man giving the groom the finger?

467
00:22:06,630 --> 00:22:07,860
Are you sure that's what he's doing?

468
00:22:09,060 --> 00:22:09,980
Who are you?

469
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:13,480
Oh,sorry,this is Karl Dupree from Secret Service-- he's working with me.

470
00:22:13,870 --> 00:22:15,740
I'm just saying,the guy is scratching his eye.

471
00:22:16,180 --> 00:22:17,770
--Maybe his eye itches.
--No,no.

472
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:19,730
That's a gestural emblem.

473
00:22:20,170 --> 00:22:23,250
It's an unconscious gesture with a specific meaning.

474
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:26,790
Uh,Loker,pull up the politician videos with the same gestural emblem.

475
00:22:27,310 --> 00:22:30,510
Now,Senator McCain has served this country honorably.

476
00:22:30,890 --> 00:22:31,870
He has...

477
00:22:35,860 --> 00:22:38,690
What letter grade would you give yourself as secretary of defense?

478
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:41,820
Oh,I'll let history worry about that.

479
00:22:42,260 --> 00:22:43,990
That's hostility.

480
00:22:47,090 --> 00:22:49,210
Now,I know why those two felt that way.

481
00:22:49,580 --> 00:22:50,500
The question is...

482
00:22:51,910 --> 00:22:53,110
Why does the best man?

483
00:22:58,760 --> 00:22:59,860
I don't know what you're talking about.

484
00:23:00,210 --> 00:23:02,340
Yeah,you do. I didn't have a fight

485
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:04,150
with Won-Hee-- I don't know why you're saying I did.

486
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:05,340
'Cause I've seen you.

487
00:23:05,420 --> 00:23:06,910
You've shown us three different ways already.

488
00:23:13,610 --> 00:23:14,300
I get it.

489
00:23:14,740 --> 00:23:16,950
You were mad at Won-Hee, and he got hurt.

490
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:18,880
And now you feel guilty.

491
00:23:19,390 --> 00:23:20,960
You wonder if,in some way, you're to blame.

492
00:23:21,370 --> 00:23:22,460
But you know that's not true.

493
00:23:25,190 --> 00:23:29,070
And the best way to help him now is to help us find the person who did hurt him.

494
00:23:33,850 --> 00:23:35,570
He owes me $5,000.

495
00:23:35,970 --> 00:23:37,770
That doesn't explain what you're feeling.

496
00:23:37,810 --> 00:23:39,110
It's not about the money.

497
00:23:43,460 --> 00:23:44,770
He has a gambling problem.

498
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:46,720
Not many people know.

499
00:23:46,750 --> 00:23:47,840
He keeps it quiet.

500
00:23:47,880 --> 00:23:51,080
He's terrified his mother's family is going to find out.

501
00:23:51,950 --> 00:23:53,770
They're old-school Korean-- they'd cut him off

502
00:23:53,790 --> 00:23:54,850
if they knew what he was doing.

503
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:58,680
A few weeks ago,he asked me to loan the five to get a bookie off his back.

504
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:00,050
I gave it to him.

505
00:24:00,480 --> 00:24:03,100
Then,I found out he didn't pay the debt,he put the money on another game.

506
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:05,770
That's when I got mad.

507
00:24:08,460 --> 00:24:10,080
I... I don't know how much he owes altogether now,

508
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:13,240
but someone talked about hurting him.

509
00:24:14,780 --> 00:24:15,510
I know that.

510
00:24:18,320 --> 00:24:19,100
There you go.

511
00:24:19,940 --> 00:24:20,820
Feel better now?

512
00:24:25,370 --> 00:24:27,110
All right,we ran the groom's banking records.

513
00:24:27,540 --> 00:24:28,840
Backs up what the kid told you.

514
00:24:28,910 --> 00:24:31,670
Busted credit,large cash deposits at erratic intervals.

515
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:33,120
Sounds like gambling addiction.

516
00:24:33,620 --> 00:24:34,820
We need to talk to the ambassador.

517
00:24:34,840 --> 00:24:35,990
Well,go ahead,he's up in the residence.

518
00:24:36,020 --> 00:24:37,020
He just got there.

519
00:24:37,450 --> 00:24:39,040
I got to put down the riot that's brewing here.

520
00:24:40,550 --> 00:24:41,780
We don't have much time left.

521
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:43,810
Hey,you want me to keep talking to people or what?

522
00:24:43,870 --> 00:24:45,630
No,go help Loker with the tapes.

523
00:24:47,170 --> 00:24:48,930
I need you to stay in holding.

524
00:24:48,990 --> 00:24:50,050
Don't give me that.

525
00:24:50,100 --> 00:24:51,080
I want to leave now!

526
00:24:51,150 --> 00:24:52,570
Sir,sir, there is nothing that I can do for you.

527
00:24:52,990 --> 00:24:54,990
I am special counsel at the White House.

528
00:24:55,040 --> 00:24:56,070
I could have your job.

529
00:24:56,810 --> 00:24:59,360
Now,are you going to let me out of here or not? Sir...

530
