00:35:51,490 --> 00:35:52,290
It was great.

805
00:35:52,360 --> 00:35:53,850
Very thorough.

806
00:35:54,460 --> 00:35:58,930
In fact,the only person we didn't see on the footage was you,

807
00:36:00,910 --> 00:36:02,570
the cameramen, which makes sense.

808
00:36:02,610 --> 00:36:04,620
I mean,cameraman's not supposed to be on camera,right?

809
00:36:05,070 --> 00:36:09,210
Now,I talked earlier about an expression that's displayed

810
00:36:09,700 --> 00:36:11,670
when you're about to commit an act of violence.

811
00:36:12,190 --> 00:36:16,810
There's also an expression that's triggered by the motive behind that violence.

812
00:36:17,300 --> 00:36:19,260
For example,when you went to see your ex-wife,

813
00:36:19,310 --> 00:36:22,690
and she told you she was going to get remarried to some rich guy,

814
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:26,910
and she didn't care how you felt,because,

815
00:36:27,750 --> 00:36:31,300
as far as she was concerned, you were nothing.

816
00:36:34,630 --> 00:36:35,790
You've been replaced.

817
00:36:38,980 --> 00:36:43,360
Now when you think back to that moment,

818
00:36:44,750 --> 00:36:45,760
and the anger

819
00:36:47,430 --> 00:36:48,700
that you felt...

820
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:54,470
...your face...

821
00:36:55,780 --> 00:36:57,350
It shows in your face.

822
00:37:16,380 --> 00:37:17,490
We were married.

823
00:37:18,640 --> 00:37:19,940
That's supposed to be for life.

824
00:37:21,170 --> 00:37:22,670
Isn't that what getting married means?

825
00:37:23,570 --> 00:37:24,760
For better or worse?

826
00:37:25,570 --> 00:37:26,940
Richer or poorer?

827
00:37:28,220 --> 00:37:29,380
Sickness and health?

828
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:34,110
Right?

829
00:37:38,200 --> 00:37:39,540
He's former military.

830
00:37:39,930 --> 00:37:41,970
He and Phoebe were married four years ago.

831
00:37:42,010 --> 00:37:43,620
Her name was Carla DiMeo then.

832
00:37:44,090 --> 00:37:44,850
They divorced.

833
00:37:44,920 --> 00:37:46,980
She changed her name, moved to D.C.

834
00:37:47,070 --> 00:37:48,660
He tracked her down a couple months ago.

835
00:37:48,700 --> 00:37:49,940
How did he get through security?

836
00:37:50,430 --> 00:37:52,420
Well,he probably spent months planning this.

837
00:37:52,480 --> 00:37:53,580
He was obsessed.

838
00:37:53,620 --> 00:37:56,250
He remachined his pistol to break apart in smaller pieces.

839
00:37:56,330 --> 00:37:58,110
It looked like camera equipment inside his bag.

840
00:37:58,170 --> 00:37:59,220
That's romantic.

841
00:37:59,380 --> 00:38:00,270
Aronson?

842
00:38:01,150 --> 00:38:01,780
Excuse me.

843
00:38:03,500 --> 00:38:06,010
Dr. Lightman. Dr. Foster.

844
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:10,270
Thank you so much.

845
00:38:17,480 --> 00:38:19,340
I saw them take Howard away.

846
00:38:20,240 --> 00:38:21,880
Did he hurt somebody else?

847
00:38:22,340 --> 00:38:22,870
No.

848
00:38:24,170 --> 00:38:26,470
I had no idea he was here during the wedding.

849
00:38:26,970 --> 00:38:28,720
I would have said something if I had.

850
00:38:29,760 --> 00:38:31,900
I never meant to lie to anybody.

851
00:38:32,830 --> 00:38:34,860
It didn't even feel like lying,really.

852
00:38:34,910 --> 00:38:35,880
It's just...

853
00:38:36,780 --> 00:38:39,480
I was so unhappy when I left Michigan,

854
00:38:39,550 --> 00:38:41,950
and changing my name,and pretending

855
00:38:42,020 --> 00:38:46,800
like none of it happened-- it was just such a relief.

856
00:38:50,340 --> 00:38:51,910
Tell Won-Hee...

857
00:38:59,010 --> 00:39:00,250
Won-Hee is awake.

858
00:39:02,430 --> 00:39:03,520
He's asking for you.

859
00:39:06,480 --> 00:39:07,610
We should go see him.

860
00:39:10,060 --> 00:39:10,950
Okay.

861
00:39:50,330 --> 00:39:50,980
Hey.

862
00:39:53,130 --> 00:39:54,050
Full day,huh?

863
00:39:55,860 --> 00:39:57,940
Want to get a drink,celebrate?

864
00:40:02,130 --> 00:40:03,450
I don't think that's a good idea.

865
00:40:05,390 --> 00:40:06,790
Didn't we get past the tough talk?

866
00:40:06,890 --> 00:40:08,500
Yeah,we did.

867
00:40:09,350 --> 00:40:10,490
Still don't think it's a good idea.

868
00:40:12,950 --> 00:40:16,200
You know,we were briefed on your team before you guys came in,

869
00:40:16,250 --> 00:40:18,630
and,uh,I know what you can do,and

870
00:40:19,410 --> 00:40:20,450
it doesn't scare me.

871
00:40:21,670 --> 00:40:22,730
I got nothing to hide.

872
00:40:23,920 --> 00:40:25,210
So,come on. It's just a drink.

873
00:40:28,370 --> 00:40:29,730
The problem is...

874
00:40:30,870 --> 00:40:31,780
I like you.

875
00:40:32,210 --> 00:40:33,410
And that's a problem because?

876
00:40:33,870 --> 00:40:35,960
Because it'll be more than just a drink.

877
00:40:36,840 --> 00:40:38,940
And then it'll get complicated.

878
00:40:40,640 --> 00:40:42,680
I'll know every lie you tell, which means,

879
00:40:42,740 --> 00:40:43,930
I'll know everything about you.

880
00:40:47,090 --> 00:40:48,370
You sure you're up for that?

881
00:40:49,300 --> 00:40:50,070
I'm in.

882
00:40:52,540 --> 00:40:53,600
Okay then.

883
00:40:53,670 --> 00:40:55,960
Uh,yeah,yeah. Maybe 20 minutes.

884
00:40:56,480 --> 00:40:57,640
No,I made a reservation.

885
00:40:58,530 --> 00:40:59,870
Okay. I'll see you there.

886
00:41:03,660 --> 00:41:04,470
Date night?

887
00:41:04,910 --> 00:41:05,820
Sort of.

888
00:41:05,900 --> 00:41:07,530
More of an apology date,really.

889
00:41:08,550 --> 00:41:09,890
What are you apologizing for?

890
00:41:09,990 --> 00:41:11,730
Oh,he asked for my help getting out of the embassy,

891
00:41:11,810 --> 00:41:12,630
and I turned him down.

892
00:41:13,110 --> 00:41:14,750
Now,you're not supposed to do that when you're married.

893
00:41:14,810 --> 00:41:15,390
You remember?

894
00:41:16,250 --> 00:41:17,180
You did the right thing.

895
00:41:18,530 --> 00:41:19,820
Oh,you're not my husband.

896
00:41:20,710 --> 00:41:22,950
Alec's trying to move up at State,which means doing

897
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:25,460
favors for your bosses and getting to the right meetings,

898
00:41:25,520 --> 00:41:26,820
which I could have helped him with.

899
00:41:26,860 --> 00:41:30,140
But I had to follow the rules and be the good girl,so...

900
00:41:30,610 --> 00:41:34,650
I'm gonna pour him a glass of wine and say I'm sorry.

901
00:41:36,210 --> 00:41:36,980
Marriage.

902
00:41:37,880 --> 00:41:39,290
Okay,I'll see you tomorrow.

903
00:41:41,910 --> 00:41:42,810
Hey,Foster?

904
00:41:43,350 --> 00:41:43,850
What?

905
00:41:46,340 --> 00:41:47,690
I don't think you're the good girl.

906
00:41:50,180 --> 00:41:50,900
Liar.

